“Monkey’s Wedding” out next week Friday! We had a term in South Africa, where I was born, for when it was raining and sunny at the same time. We called it a Monkey’s Wedding! Presave link in bio and stories! 
📷 @itstylerrowell 
🎨 me

Monkey’s Wedding out on Friday!!! 
Presave in bio and stories !!! 🖤
📷 @itstylerrowell

“Monkey’s Wedding” it out now on all streaming platforms!! And on Bandcamp 🖤🖤🖤
📷 @itstylerrowell 
🎨 me

Thank you all for the love on Monkey’s Wedding!! After Spirals came out, I had this real moment of feeling creatively stuck. I had said so many things (musically) in that album and it left me feeling  frozen in the studio, not knowing what I wanted to make . I  decided to have a creative day, but to just focus on simple simple simple . I got out my kalimba , shakers, tambarines, bass guitar, looper pedals etc and started playing around . This little riff came out and I started layering things and the instrumental birthed. “oh it’s a monkey’s wedding”, was a stream of conscious lyric , but brought me right back to childhood in South Africa . We used to call , when it’s a raining and sunny at the same time , a “monkey’s wedding!”
Thanks all for continuing to support me ! Truly means the world . 
Lyrics : 

Woman, come home, 
I'm tired of sleeping alone. 
Oh it's a monkey's wedding! 
The sun is shining through, 
The clouds are raining , 
I found you in the blue 

Somewhere there's a child,
Running home mother's smile
Oh it's a monkey's wedding! 
The sun is shining through, 
The clouds are raining , 
I found you in the blue 

Much love and gratitude for @itstylerrowell for hoping on to figure out the artwork for this one . Such a memorable day taking photos and painting. You’re the best Tyler! 
Also shout out @spotify for the playlist ad!! This is my first independent release since I first put out Lonely Shade of Blue so this support means the world 🖤

Happy new year everyone !!! 
Just want to say a quick thank you, from the bottom of my heart , to all of you for continuing to support me music ! 
Went on my first headline tour , did a bunch of piano shows, put out the Vinyl for Spirals , put out a couple new tunes , and got some amazing tv spots, and many other things and etc etc etc etc 
Probably my biggest highlight was hearing from all of you and reading your words of encouragement and support . I feel so privledged to have an audience for my musical explorations . It’s a weird thing spending your life in a small studio . It feels sometimes like the music never really leaves my walls , and validation is given through pixels on an phone. so, hearing from you, having you guys reach out for vinyl and Merch, asking me to go on tour again, tagging me in videos and even learning to play my music on the piano, absolutely blows my mind . So, thank you!!! 
Thank you so much for also supporting my two new singles, Monkeys Wedding and Trip to Mars . I know 2023 wasn’t the year for a lot of output of new music, but rest assured there wasn’t a week that went by that I wasn’t working on something new . Just know if ever I disappear, it’s because I’m in my cave working on something new haha. 
It’s kinda weird because , on one hand I’m feeling anxious that I didn’t drop lots of new music, but on another hand , I spent so much time exploring  new sonic places / production /rhythms/ harmonics that I have a new level of excitement coming into this new year . Currently have a notes on my phone  with 50+ new tunes and song ideas . :) Hoping to get that all shipped out to you same day-overnight-express-dhl- this year . 
Anything you’d guys love to hear/see from me in2024 ? 
Btw I am so bad at doing these write up things so, I apologize if this blurb makes zero sense and is a labyrinth of repetitive run-on sentences and grammatical errors .
